 pretty symmetry and pretty symmetry is easy to hear. Walk the under-stairs like you are late to a promise and too proud to run, and you might just carry this note without us having to cut you down later for swinging in the open.\"},\n    {\"speaker\": \"Hark Tamsin\", \"lines\": \"Clerks are the hinges on which verdict doors swing, and I am a hinge that prefers oil to rust, so keep your packet clean and your name quieter still. The bench will not touch contraband parchment that smells of Orchids’ perfume or Aerarium cedar, and they will toss it back into your hands as if it were a hot coal if it looks too clever by half. I can slide it onto the dais beneath the presiding’s left elbow between petitions, but only if you time your approach to the bell’s first toll, because the Court’s protocol is a choreography and you cannot step on the master’s feet. If a marshal bars your path, show the braid on Saela’s seal and speak as if you’re trying not to speak at all, because humility is the sharpest disguise we allow behind the rail. Should the wind falter and the bell strain, take your breath from your knees and not your throat, because that is where courage lives when a city is listening.\"}\n  ],\n  \"choices\": [\n    {\"id\": \"C1\", \"title\": \"Walk the under-stairs alone and silent\", \"text\": \"You thread the amphitheater’s bowels without calling in favors, trusting only your ear for the Old Song and the glide of your whispercloak across iron ribs. Each step is counted against the ratchet’s click, and each pause is measured to the heartbeat of guards who do not know they are pacing your breath. You plant the true-note chimes low in the vent throats where old dust hides the shine of fresh metal, choosing asymmetry so Orchid eddy-benders cannot predict your lattice. The sealed packet rides high and tight under your collarbone, its wax catching sweat like a second pulse, and you time your ascent to shadow the procession of advocates as cover. When the moment comes, y